I cannot say. 1048 Aere interp. cet: Lucr. is here completely mistaken from too hasty an induction: neither the attractive nor the repulsive power of a magnet is sensibly affected by the interposition of any body which is not sensibly magnetical, be it metal glass wood paper or whatever else: nay the mag- net works equally in a vacuum, the absence or presence of air making no difference: this by the way overthrows the poet's argument 1022— 1041, where he brings in his favourite air to assist in explaining the attraction between the loadstone and iron.
